Notes: Jim writes : "...his solicitors requested from the police the briefs of the evidence of the witness..." In New Zealand the expression "briefs of evidence" is commonly used to describe what are usually called "proofs" in England. Cooke P. (1988) 1 <i>New Zealand Law Reports</i> p. 387
